HEADWORD: Microseme
<hw>Mi"cro*seme</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Micro-</ets>
+ Gr. <?/ sign, mark: cf. F. <ets>micros⟦egrave⟧me</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Having the orbital index relatively small;
having the orbits broad transversely; -- opposed to
<ant>megaseme</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
